  "evidence_entities": [
    {
      "id": "paper_id:background:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": null,
      "text": "DDR-IF-high tumors were characterized by a distinct biological profile, including (i) transcriptional exhaustion of the cGAS-STING innate immune pathway (p < 0.001), (ii) significantly reduced CD8+ T cell infiltration (2.3-fold fewer, p = 0.004), and (iii) a superior pooled objective response rate to PARP-ICB combinations (42% vs 18%; risk ratio 2.3, 95% CI 1.3-4.2; p = 0.003).",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "systematic review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:methods:3:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": null,
      "text": "The final DDR-IF score was defined using standardized coefficients: DDR-IF = 0.4 \u00d7 (HRD score) + 0.35 \u00d7 log10(TMB + 1) + 0.25 \u00d7 (STING activation score), where all predictors were z-score normalized prior to model fitting.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "systematic review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:results:4:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": null,
      "text": "A meta-analysis of six trials (2020\u20132024) confirmed that DDR-IF-high tumors (e.g., ATM/BRCA1/2-altered) show a 2.3-fold higher ORR to PARP-ICB versus DDR-IF-low (42% vs. 18%, p=0.003).",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "systematic review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:results:5:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": null,
      "text": "In our cohort, the DDR-IF score demonstrated superior predictive power for PARP-ICB response (AUROC = 0.81) compared to SLFN11 expression alone (AUROC = 0.64), ATM mutation status (AUROC = 0.59), or a simple TMB-PD-L1 composite model (AUROC = 0.72).",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "systematic review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:results:6:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": null,
      "text": "Multiplex-IF (n=82) demonstrated that PARP1-high tumors (H-score \u2265150) exhibited 2.3-fold fewer CD8+ TILs (p=0.004) and diminished p-STING (<5% area), indicating immune-cold phenotypes.",
      "confidence": 0.85,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "systematic review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:results:7:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": null,
      "text": "In the independent MSK-IMPACT validation cohort (n=152), the DDR-IF score successfully stratified patients, with DDR-IF-high status being associated with significantly improved progression-free survival on PARP-ICB regimens (HR 0.45, 95% CI 0.22-0.91).",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "systematic review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    }
  ],
